had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Fleitel was born about 0955, in Normandy, France. He had at least 1 son with Havlive de Normandie."},"et":{"about 0955–":"umbes 0955–Surnud","0960–1034":"0960–1034","0975–1047":"0975–1047","0955–Male":"0955–Surnud","about 0955":"umbes 0955","0975":"0975","1047":"1047","0960":"0960","1034":"1034","ABT 975":"umbes 0975","0955":"0955","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Longueville-sur-Scie, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Longueville-sur-Scie, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 0955–":"noin 0955–Kuollut","0960–1034":"0960–1034","0975–1047":"0975–1047","0955–Male":"0955–Kuollut","about 0955":"noin 0955","0975":"0975","1047":"1047","0960":"0960","1034":"1034","ABT 975":"noin 0975","0955":"0955","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska","Longueville-sur-Scie, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Longueville-sur-Scie, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 0955–":"environ 0955–Décédé","0960–1034":"0960–1034","0975–1047":"0975–1047","0955–Male":"0955–Décédé","about 0955":"environ 0955","0975":"0975","1047":"1047","0960":"0960","1034":"1034","ABT 975":"environ 0975","0955":"0955","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","Longueville-sur-Scie, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Longueville-sur-Scie, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Robert Fleitel est né environ 0955, à Normandie, France. Il a eu